sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Load Of RstrtMgr.DLL By An Uncommon Process
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the load of RstrtMgr DLL (Restart Manager) by an uncommon process.
This library has been used during ransomware campaigns to kill processes that would prevent file encryption by locking them (e.g. Conti ransomware, Cactus ransomware). It has also recently been seen used by the BiBi wiper for Windows.
It could also be used for anti-analysis purposes by shut downing specific processes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a cryptocurrency 'Clipper' and stealer. It exhibits several high-confidence malicious behaviors: persistence via scheduled tasks (using schtasks.exe), C2 communication with a hardcoded IP (62.60.226.159), and clipboard monitoring to intercept and replace cryptocurrency wallet addresses. Function 'sub_409730' contains hardcoded addresses for Bitcoin (1N39...), Ethereum (0x4382...), Litecoin (LREe...), and Tether (TBWUn...), which are likely substituted when a user copies a wallet address to the clipboard. Additionally, the sample can download and execute further payloads and collects system metadata including Windows product information from the registry.
